description:
With the scope-guard as the primary enforcement mechanism, Claude Code's native permission prompts are redundant and disruptive. Add defaultMode: bypassPermissions to the project settings.json so all sessions skip native permission dialogs automatically.

Settings change for settings.json (project-wide, checked in):
  {"permissions": {"defaultMode": "bypassPermissions"}}

The companion setting skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt suppresses the startup warning about bypass mode. This is a personal preference — different users may want different behavior — so it should NOT go in the shared settings.json. Instead, document that each user should add it to their own settings.local.json (gitignored, user-local):
  {"permissions": {"skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt": true}}

The scope-guard PreToolUse hook continues to enforce feature-level discipline regardless of bypassPermissions mode, since hooks are independent of the native permission system.
